storyInfo: Rhodes Island suffers an attack long planned. Reunion kidnaps Talulah and demands this 'leader' give them an explanation for her past actions.

attributes.content: 9:33 A.M. \ Foggy
Nameless Barrenlands, Inside Rhodes Island
Good morning, Closure. Here's your breakfast.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Oh, thanks!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: There's no mold or anything, right...?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Uh, probably not, I guess.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: *Sigh*... We've been stuck here for days thanks to this shitty weather... Who knows how bad this'll throw off our schedule... Hmm, this flavor...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I mean, a Catastrophe caused this thick fog... It's not going to be good if we end up coming head to head with an aftershock.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Should I turn in the environmental Originium monitoring report for last night right now?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Where's Kal'tsit? Is she still in the operating theater?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Yes, she's been there since last night.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Don't worry about it right now, then.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Thank you.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Can I help you with anything else?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Hm... Let's see. Wanna finish this health food for me? I mean it. This stuff's got a real funny taste.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Eh?! You want me to eat all that?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Haha, calm down. Just kidding.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: What's the matter?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: New mail? Out in the wasteland?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Is there a town or a Messenger Outpost close by?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: No... If there was, we would've been in contact with them a couple days ago...
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: That's weird. Let's see...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: The sender's Dijkstra... What, Dijkstra?! I thought he was in Columbia!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.text: TO Closure
Dear Closure, it's been a while.
How's things? Going well? The last time we worked together was back in summer, right?
I was really shocked when Grace got in touch with me and told me about your plan. Screwing around with Kazimierz corporate networks isn't exactly small potatoes.
I gotta hand it to you, though. That's exactly your style. Either way, it was a good time, second only to that hit we did in Columbia once! It was perfect!

attributes.content: Acute lesions successfully removed.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Keep the infusion going.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Wound is clean...
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Hold on, confirm the patient's vitals.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Okay...!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Doctor! The patient's heart rate is abnormal... Body... body temperature is dropping!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Calm down.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Adjust transmural pressure. I need an injection intervention right now.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Prepare to stop the bleeding.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.text: But you know. It doesn't matter how many banks we hack, how many millionaires we screw with. Even if we manage to take control of half the city's drones, put a stop to all the machines, and scare the cowards shitless—
It's all just fleeting, and anything fleeting might as well be pointless.
Before I forget, Closure. There's something I need to tell you.
There was this one time I mentioned a friend of mine who's got Oripathy. Do you remember?

attributes.content: Hey, everyone... It's time to change shift.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Blaze!
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: Did something happen?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Nope... Well, given this visibility, the surveillance equipment's about the only thing we can trust.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: I doubt even the sniper operators on lookout can see anything in this weather...
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: Eh, you're right. All this fog is a major buzzkill...
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Stormeye wouldn't have much trouble with the fog. If only he had left just two weeks later. Too bad.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: It's been a few days since we stopped, though. If anything's gonna happen, it should already have happened by now.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: You guys should head back and get some rest.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Yeah, sure.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.text: That man was as healthy as could be.
He had a decent education and a decent job. He was married, though no kids.
He didn't even know how he caught Oripathy. He just showed up to work one morning to find a posting on the company notice board about his infection. Everyone started looking at him different.
To tell the truth, I was too lazy to look into it all that much. Someone was either jealous, or they were trying set him up, some kind of infighting.
Anyway, after that, his life was ruined. He lost his job, and his wife left him. How can you blame them, though? We all know Oripathy's infectious.

I just met him by chance, and I decided to help him on a whim too. Making a few quick changes to a database here or there isn't much for people like us, you know. A few keystrokes and we change a man's fate. Almost magical, huh?
So, that's what I figured. I thought it was unfair, so I did that for him.
I thought I was helping him.
But things didn't unfold quite like I expected.
He didn't go back to the life he once had.
I met the guy again in the barrenlands outside Columbia. He had joined an Infected organization. He told me his comrades in Ursus needed his help, and that's why he went there.

attributes.content: An Infected organization...?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Hmm... So this guy got caught up with the Infected too?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.text: Closure, take a guess what I'm trying to tell you with this story.
Eyes.
They went to great lengths to find me, but I still didn't know the slightest thing about the Infected.
They were travel-worn, their equipment was outdated, and most of them were malnourished—
But their eyes were full of light.
Closure, it took us a long time to find this ray of light. A very, very long time.
Anger, unwillingness, the readiness to make sacrifices for a belief, the mind to give your life for a certain cause.
Same as you and your buddies over there. We want to change something. We know what's wrong.

attributes.content: 'That's why I decided to help them. Columbia, Kazimierz, and the Sarkaz homeland you told me all about—'
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: 'That's what we've always been doing. Always, even—'
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: '—Now.'
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: ...That's it?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Is that supposed to be it? Hold on, what do you mean, 'Now?'
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Whoa! What just happened?!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: The tremor... came from below. It was huge, too—An explosion?!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Ahh! Wh-What's going on?!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: We told everyone ahead of time how difficult this surgery was going to be. We told them we needed absolute silence!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Uh, this is the operating theater... What?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: The security door's been... What?! All the bulkheads are locked? Huh? That's...
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Stay calm.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Contact all the operators we can. Tell them to head to confinement immediately.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Also, tell Blaze that she may damage the ship's facilities as necessary.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: R-Right!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Everyone else, continue the operation.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: We'll leave what's going on outside to the other operators.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: There is nothing more important than the patient's life in the operating room. Don't get distracted.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Ah, I'm truly sorry! I'll get ready right away!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I thought this would've been more difficult.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: But this must be our first formal meeting, 'Leader' of Reunion.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: You are... Reunion.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: You don't seem very surprised.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: I simply know better than anyone that the fires of Infected fury cannot be extinguished so easily.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: It's just...
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: —It's been a while, 'Leader.'
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: It's you...!
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Don't remember me? Ha, of course you don't! I was just a nameless pawn, someone lucky enough to avoid letting you kill me back in Chernobog!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: But you, Talulah, our 'Leader!' I will never forget your damned face!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: You joined us when our team passed through the village that was destroyed by the taxmen. Your name is... Valiya.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: You remember my name, huh...? So, what about Leontyev, Denis, and Arseny? Do you remember them? Do you know what happened to them?
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: I'm here because I want to ask you myself: Why did you do what you did?! Who gave you the right?! How could you betray us?!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: Let go of her collar.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Now's not the time. We need to leave this place first.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Hmph.
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: You heard him, Leader of the Infected.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: We all want answers. Many of us have suffered waiting for this chance. The chance to get them from you.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Don't forget. Those who most deserve to judge you, to hear out your defense, and to determine your fate, are the Infected who rose and died for you.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Talulah, you need to come with us.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Closure! Are you okay?! What was that just now?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: What kind of sick joke is this?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Closure?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: You've gotta be kidding me! He's definitely somewhere close by. He paralyzed Rhodes Island's systems!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: The surveillance... and observation systems... Hah, not bad...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I got a transmission from Logistics! Some of the operators have been ambushed by... R-Reunion!
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: No way! Reunion?!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: No, no, no—Hurry! Tell Amiya right now. They might be here for Talulah! I'll get these systems back up. We need to act fast!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Y-Yes, ma'am!
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Why am I getting a message now, of all times?!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Argh! My control screen's locked?!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Good morning. Good morning?
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: Hard at work fixing your system, Closure? You're kinda mad right now, aren't you?
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: Oh, I should probably mention this video's prerecorded. You don't have to waste time tracing me.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: Oh, also, I went through the trouble of keeping your Medical Department's system modules separate when I did all the prep work overnight. Spares the innocent, you know? I'm a stand-up guy, aren't I?
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: Dijkstra—!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Sorry about this, Closure. I know it's pretty unchill to nail you with this hookup you so graciously gave me. But still...
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: I'd do it again. You know me. No regrets.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: When you gave me the prototype back then, you said it was, at the time, the best option for taking down Columbian network programs. You called it your trump card.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: And doing my wetwork the past couple days, I realized you weren't lying. Rhodes Island's security system works very similar to the logic you handed me.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: So yeah, I abused your trust, no doubt about that. But you've got your position, I got my judgment. That's how it goes.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: I still remember how I met you, just a Sarkaz back then, and how we became friends.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: I hope we're still friends... Or, like before, war buddies.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: —That said, Closure.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: First and foremost, I'm a rebel. We've always been rebels. Always will be.
attributes.name: Dijkstra

attributes.content: Where do you get off... c'mon, so damned full of yourself!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: No... Now's not the time to worry about this. Is the comm system still working?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: All stations!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Grr, if Ascalon and Logos were here, you wouldn't be running around like you own the place—
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: —Hey! Get out here!
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: I know you're hiding on both sides of the hallway, but this is Rhodes Island, and you aren't fooling me!
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Right, Blaze, this is Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: It was this very same corridor where I first saw you and the other elite operators come home after a triumphant victory.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: Guard...?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: I hesitated. When I first learned about the plan to attack Rhodes Island. Of course I hesitated.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: I'm not going to justify it, but I think this is exactly why I have to come back. Both to take responsibility and to bear witness to this plan's execution.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: 'Responsibility...' huh?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Right. If I'm here, I can't make excuses.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: If there's even a single operator who thinks it, then I am indeed a 'traitor.'
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: So you're with Reunion now... what are you doing back here?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: The few survivors who managed to make it out of Ursus drifted out in the borderless barrenlands.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: First we got to Columbia, then Leithanien, and then Siracusa, Victoria... All these countries... there were Infected trying to get in touch with us.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: Reunion managed to set a fire, and from the tundra all across the world.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: But... what are we supposed to tell the Infected who chose to stand up for our cause because of Talulah, and to the Infected who chose to stand up against fate because of the Ursus Reunion Movement—
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: How do we break it to them that we failed in Chernobog, and that Reunion was yet another pawn, tossed away by the great powers once it exhausted its usefulness?
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: There are way too many Infected left in the dark, Infected who lost friends and loved ones.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: That's why Reunion needs that truth. They need the 'leader' to answer to them.
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: And then...
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: Then, we will start all over.
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: —Sarkaz?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: No, you're no ordinary mercenaries—
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Damned straight.
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: I heard that nutjob W started chumming with you guys after that? Well, whatever.
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: After the Captain died, not all of the guerrilla fighters decided to part ways with Reunion...
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: Hand Talulah over. If Reunion still exists, then she belongs to us.
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: ...Hah.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: You think we're gonna talk this over and come to a nice agreement?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Yeah, that's not gonna happen.
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: Talulah's got Lungmenite and Rhodes Islander blood on her hands, but let's not forget there's blood on your hands too. The Captain's, and Yelena's.
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: Don't you think for a second we'll go easy on you.
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: Nine, the barriers have been activated. This whole area's sealed off. We just need to deal with the hostiles in here ASAP.
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: Good. Get the team ready for rendezvous and exfiltration.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Sure thing.
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: The enemies are fighting back. We don't have enough manpower—
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: We're not fighting for the sake of fighting here. Prioritize the evacuation!
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: In your dreams! You aren't getting away that easily!
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: Don't even think about it!
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: Ugh, why can't this ever be easy.
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: Boss, you go on ahead!
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: Right. Be sure to catch up. I'll see you later.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Confirm the exfiltration route!
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Confirmed. No trouble at all! We'll make it out of here without a hitch if we keep to the plan!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: Good, contact the team outside. The plan is a go!
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Roger!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: Hold it!
—Stop. You are not leaving.
I won't let you through.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Talulah, you should not have left that room.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Are these—Reunion? Are they here to rescue you?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: The leader of Rhodes Island herself. Well, the word 'rescue' isn't very appropriate here, not that it matters.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Now I do hope you'll understand. She's coming with us, and she doesn't have a choice.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: No, she's staying here.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Ursus and Lungmen both have a right to prosecute Talulah, and naturally Rhodes Island has a reason to imprison her.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: But Talulah also owes us an explanation. To Reunion... and to the Infected.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: —In that case, why not trust Rhodes Island, and wait until Talulah can give you that explanation?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: That's the same thing Guard said to us, he wanted us to trust you.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: And Ch'en... Lungmen's Superintendent Ch'en once said she wanted to create fair terms by which an Infected like her could be judged.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: But what even counts as fair?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Chernobog and Lungmen have seen so much sacrifice, so much needless death. Even if she had a thousand excuses, she's still guilty.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Rhodes Island is welcome to forge that future, to wait for it to come, but... Reunion, the ones she betrayed... they don't get a say?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Answer me, as Rhodes Island's leader.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: In that case, we can wait together.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: The Shieldguards are willing to believe... and so do Rhodes Island's operators... that there will come a day we give everyone an answer...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: But, right now, Reunion is trying to snatch her away from Rhodes Island through violence. How is anyone supposed to trust in Reunion?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: I don't want the Infected to see any more bloodshed. I don't want to fight the Reunion Movement again. But why must you—
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Even if I'm willing to wait, and there are others who are... 'Reunion' cannot wait.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: That's all I have to say.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Nine! We have to move! We can't waste any more time with her!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: Let's go, Talulah.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Wait, you can't—
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: That's not for you to decide!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: Everyone, stop the Cautus! Watch her Arts!
attributes.name: Reunion Soldier

attributes.content: You're strong, Rhodes Island Infected! There's no way I could stop you alone!
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: Heh, I'll take that as a compliment. That mean you're letting me by?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: No, I was just thinking that at least Yelena gave her life fighting a true warrior!
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: Aw, too bad. I'm in a hurry, though. So you guys are in for a hard time!
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: —Crossbowman, stop her!
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: There's more of you—?!
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Wait—You—? What's that you're holding?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: The captain's crossbow. You've been taking good care of it.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: Thank you.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: But as long as we choose to stand up, it's too early for that crossbow to be sealed away as a mere memento of the dead.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: All hands, ready.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: This rabbit... She's so young. How is she this powerful?!
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: *Pant*... *pant*...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Out of... the way!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Heh... I signed up for this ambush ready to sacrifice myself.
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: Come, Cautus. I saw your battle at the core city. Honestly, I admire you people.
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: But I won't give in. Even if the Infected have to die here.
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: I—
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: It's flowering season.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: A-Are those... flowers? When did—
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: You take nonlethal shots, even at a time like this.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: You're a worthy leader, Rhodes Island, but it's about time you got some sleep.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: (You... can't...)
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Um, can your Arts work a little faster...? I mean, how much time is this going to buy us?
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: Enough. Have all teams move to our current position. The aircraft will be here—
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Wait! Nine! Dijkstra says he's got something approaching us fast on the camera feed!
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: Are there other operators...?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: No, no! That's not human!
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: (Elated roar)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: S-Stop that thing! It's after Nine and Talulah—
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: (Relaxedly stretches its limbs)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: (Howls)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: Woah!
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: Just what... is that—?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: (Roars)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: (Crap! My Arts can't—)
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: (Taunting roar)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: Silence isn't an answer, Reunion.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Now, here's my answer. Not that I am given a choice, as you said.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Nine! We don't have the time! We can't hold that Feline and the monster for very long!
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: (Roars)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: Ugh—Dammit!
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: 30 seconds more...
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Hngh.... Mmm...?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: (Agitated roars)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: It's charging you again, Nine—
attributes.name: Guerrilla Sarkaz

attributes.content: Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: I'm not going to convince anyone, nor will I force anyone to accept what I think.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: But it's not over yet.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: I will wait for that day to come. Whether it's the day she spoke of, or the day you did. I will wait for my so-called judgment.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: But until then—
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Flames rise from her fingertips.
Like a great wall built of fury.
—(Brief timid moans)!
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: I will live.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.options: Don't touch her!;Over my dead body!

attributes.content: You step in front of Amiya, shielding her.
The suffocatingly high temperature briefly dazes you, though the fire's sparks continue to dance in the air, leaving you two unharmed.
Relax, I made sure the flames went around her.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: You still have a long road ahead. I can only hope... nothing will cloud your hearts.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: It's time! Nine! We can't wait any longer!
attributes.name: Guard

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Well, then... We'll meet again, Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Take that thing down.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: (Howls)
attributes.name: Mon3tr

attributes.content: A Columbian low-altitude aircraft. They've been waiting for foggy weather.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Set Amiya down on the floor. Quick.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: So that's Kal'tsit.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Guard said that if, including Kal'tsit, there were just three elite operators around, our ambush wouldn't have worked.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: That's why today... that was our only chance.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: How long have you been preparing for this?
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: A long time.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: So? Where are we going?
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Where it all started.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Mmgh...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Calm down... She passed out. That's all.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: It's no mere Arts, though. It might be plant toxins... Blaze.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Take Amiya to Medical.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Alright...
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: I can see it on your face. Don't blame yourself. That Sarkaz was no run-of-the-mill fighter.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: But I still let them get away.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: If... If only I had gotten more answers out of Guard—!
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Guard...
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: They came prepared, and we weren't.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: H-Hey, everybody? How's everything—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: A—Amiya...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Let's get a damage report and take care of the wounded first. We'll talk about the rest later.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: That guy played me like a fiddle... This ambush could've been avoided.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Dammit...! I gave him that thing because I trusted him—!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Dr. Kal'tsit!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I am listening.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: This ship... Rhodes Island might be finding itself under frequent, direct threats, just like we used to!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I want to hold an emergency meeting right now.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: We'll be entering Victoria soon...
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: We don't have many operators at your disposal.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Well then... Doctor.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: I'll have you assist Closure. That look on her face... it's seldom seen.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: At least you stood up and shielded Amiya in the end.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Thank you.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: What's this...?
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Your new cuffs.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: They track your position in real time. And if you try to use your Arts again, you aren't going to enjoy it.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Talulah, you are our prisoner.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: When did you join Reunion, Lungmenite?
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Every soul who walks this world is fated to die, let alone the Infected, and let alone me.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: That said, the humiliation the Infected have faced and the fury of the enslaved have not been answered for.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: That's why I can't die for nothing.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: When this comes to an end, you will die.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Then let our brethren tear down the banners of the old era and set all injustice and tyranny ablaze. Then, and only then, scatter their ashes on my grave.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: But I know, of course, what you and your followers seek first is the truth.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: It's like you and Ch'en were cut from the same cloth.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: You know her.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: I do. And not just Superintendent Ch'en. I know Ch'en Hui-chieh. So I can tell you two are alike.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: That's for another time, though.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Sorry, everyone... I made you worry.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Amiya! Are you okay?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Yeah...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: I... I couldn't stop Talulah.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Reunion has been tracking our ship under cover of fog and Catastrophe for at least a dozen days, and they had infiltrated our systems long before that... They didn't make their move right away, and instead waited until we were least prepared.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: We will get Talulah back, but it's not necessarily a bad thing that Lungmen and Ursus no longer have a reason to keep track of the Rhodes Island landship.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: We're getting closer and closer to Victoria, Amiya.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: We are...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: If he managed to take my systems down... then I can trace him too.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: He couldn't wipe all the records in time. There's gotta be some clues he left behind, like an origin terminal, geolocation info, and how he forged everything—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Just watch! I will find them!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.options: Sorry, Amiya.;......;I wasn't able to do anything for you.

attributes.content: It's okay...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: It's strange... Dr. Kal'tsit, Closure, Doctor. I'm getting a weird feeling about this turn of events.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.options: What?;......;What a coincidence. I've been getting a weird feeling too.

attributes.content: Maybe... certain things are fated to happen, and we, sooner or later, have to face them.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: I think...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: ...this isn't the end.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: —We will meet again, Talulah.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: —I found a Messenger who can help! It's one of my old—
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: Chenchen? Are you spaced off?
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Ch'en

attributes.content: It's just... I'm getting this weird feeling... Whatever.
attributes.name: Ch'en

attributes.content: Hm? Is everyone from Yan that sensitive? Got some kind of sixth sense?
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: Exactly. We solve cases with nothing but intuition alone.
attributes.name: Ch'en

attributes.content: Eh?! Can you really?
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: ...Heh.
attributes.name: Ch'en

attributes.content: Stop being an idiot. Let's go.
attributes.name: Ch'en

attributes.content: It's cold.
This cold wind and snow used to be a familiar sight, yet it all feels so foreign now.
The snow breeze carries with it many tiny grains of rock, pricking away at the Draco's face.
Ursus's tundras are so much harsher and livelier than what she faintly remembers in her fading memories.
It's cold.
How long has it been since I last felt such cold?
A few months? Half a year? A year?
Has it really...
Has it really been so long?
Like I said, why are we still keeping her alive like she did nothing wrong?!
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: Nobody wants to see Talulah hanged more than us.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: We've been through it all, over the years, from our beginnings in the tundras all the way to the end in Chernobog... how do you think we stomach her betrayal?
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: She used to... She... *sigh*.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: We don't know the whole story of Chernobog... but it's fishy, and we need a more concrete answer.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: Why should we even trust her?!
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: Leave it to Nine.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: The captain wouldn't want to see Infected morale fall to rock bottom either... but Nine is a bit more calm when it comes to this mess.
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: Of course she is! She's a Lungmenite who joined us halfway through! She doesn't know what it means to be part of Reunion—
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: —Watch your mouth!
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: Where did you think our comrades who left for the other countries started their journey?!
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: They started from the snowfields beneath your feet and made their way across the world under the watchful eyes of that disgusting traitor!
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: Do you think hanging her will solve the whole thing?!
attributes.name: Phantom Crossbowman

attributes.content: I... Sorry.
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: I'll... cool off.
attributes.name: Reunion Warrior

attributes.content: It's the Infected workmen from Londinium. They keep looking for help, trying to build relationships with other Infected.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Victoria... They rose because of you, Talulah. And that's before we even say... you are a Draco.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Just as you said, you don't have the right to die as you please. If all Reunion across the world rose up in arms because of you, then—
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: —Either the resistance thus far has been futile or... we will need some new tinder for our fire to crackle loud again.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: That's why your next destination is Victoria.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: It's more than that, Talulah.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: You still want to stay in Ursus?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: I'm looking for someone.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Someone I should've burned to ashes.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Who?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: An evil god who calls himself immortal.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: To resist him.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: You know how big this country is, don't you? You have only a few months. It's like a needle in a haystack.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: That's enough time.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: I will find him.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: You've gone quiet again, all of a sudden.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: I... remembered something.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Here we are. This is it.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: This place...
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: This used to be Reunion's stronghold.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Of course, I only heard about it from the survivors. I have no idea what it was like back then.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: What about you? Do you remember?
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: The silent warrior stops in her tracks.
Amid the vast white blanket brought forth by the Ursus winter, the abandoned stronghold is almost entirely covered in snow, leaving not a trace of its former appearance.
Even Talulah finds this strange. It is as though she can see those scenes unfolding before her. She can immediately tell where the campfire used to be.

The walk was difficult, but the team was as hardened as they could have been. The soldiers once gathered here to sing together and warm their ever-starving stomachs with a soup that had only a hint of salt for taste.
And now, where the campfire once burned, there stands solemnly a misshapen stone slab.
That's...
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: A cenotaph. It's like a monument.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: It was built by the warriors who survived.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: No matter how the living judge you, no matter what the future holds, you must return here first.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: You need to question yourself.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Nine, we've scouted the road ahead.
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: We'll go around the village to the west. We'll rendezvous with some fighters there.
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: We don't have time. Have everyone go on the double. We need to make it back to the stronghold sooner than planned.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Okay...
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: —Is something the matter?
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: I will never forget what you said to us in Chernobog, Talulah.
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: And I definitely won't forget what you did in the core city. Everything you did, every decision you made, I will have you answer for them.
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: Don't even think about running away.
attributes.name: Reunion Caster

attributes.content: You heard him. You're not safe here.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: We'll meet up with you up ahead, but you don't have much time.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Go.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: See for yourself the sacrifices you trampled and hold them in your heart. Etch them into your brain forever.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: Remember them.
attributes.name: Nine

attributes.content: The Draco begins to walk in silence. Her footsteps alone remain on the white snowfields. With each step on the thick snow, the mud below is imprinted with her weight.
Talulah walks tall with her back perfectly straight.
Aside from that one winter, when the slowly fading warmth behind her drained her of breath, she has never once slouched her back.
The names etched on the crude cenotaph appear to have been scrubbed often; they are starting to fade.

It feels as though only a brief moment has passed. At the same time, it also feels like an eternity, to the point that the world itself falls still, and that the weight of emotions falling on the mud amidst the snow can only be borne by the land.
From afar, the warrior appears as both a solemn statue and a tree growing in the snowstorm.

Her roots must dig deep into the earth. Her figure can only expose itself above the snow ever so slightly. Beneath the hidden soil, the massive roots trickling out of the Draco continue to expand and steadily take hold.
At this moment, even the silence itself is engulfed by the snowstorm.
The warrior raises her head. A snowflake flutters downward onto her cheek, dried up before it can dissolve.
The snow ended long ago, in actuality. It's hard to believe that the northern wind granted her this bit of kindness, with the clouds dispersed and the sun shining down brightly.
The weather is fine today. A rare occurrence here in the tundra.
It's cold.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Looks like I need to get used to this weather all by myself again.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Sorry, I can't take too long. I need to go now. There are many to whom I owe an explanation.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: One day, we will make it through this snowstorm and reach that end we must ultimately reach...
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: But, right now, it looks like this place needs a flame to awaken it.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: —I'd better hurry and start a fire.
attributes.name: Talulah
